					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7062029#post-3919743</guid>
				<title>im big</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7062029/scp-4420#post-3919743</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 21 Aug 2018 04:45:29 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>keyii</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4420424</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I adore you and I adore slightly wacky skips like this — I was very surprised to find myself feeling sorry for a potato!!</p> <p>I think what made this skip for me was the text messages, which had a lot of personality (“im big”), as well as the descriptions of all the stuff that the SCP grows (Michelle Brown, age 6, potato sack champion?!). It’s got that perfect charmingly weird vibe that I adore in skips! So +1 and also +my undying love and affection, though you already had that! 💕</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7062029#post-3919688</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7062029/scp-4420#post-3919688</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 21 Aug 2018 04:01:29 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>ModernMajorGeneral</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>274283</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is like <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-3127">SCP-3127</a> but not as scary, with less buildup/escalation and not as much meat (ha) on it in general. The description was a good hook but the ending relying on 'thing can magically send messages in English because it was too difficult to come up with another way to tell the story organically' rubs me the wrong way. This also happened in 3127 but was mitigated by the SCP having already been interviewed and talking throughout the rest of the article and the messages at the end being a smaller proportion of the whole thing.</p> <p>I guess what I'm trying to say is the convenient note at the end explaining everything is already annoying but having to cook up an additional power for the object in order to facilitate the note is worse.</p> <p>I don't <em>hate</em> this - I think the site has room for a lot of bizarre yet simple and mundane objects and this idea sits in a nice spot for that, but I'm not a fan of the execution.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
